  "body": "Related to #2510\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nLabels are not defined in the English language, so the English language is used as the source of truth for translations, which couples the translation of English with the definition of labels.\r\n\r\nWe could use a spec to define existent labels, which could automatically be checked somehow against the code with a task. That way we could treat English as the rest of the languages, with the exception that we could require that English always have all labels translated, since it is the language from which translations are made.",
